>   FYI How to make our EZboard take less hits </span><hr size=1> Hiyas folks, im a new ezboard user really and i just read the Monkly biz boards and wasnt aware of how the fees were determined by the amout of hits we had is what determined the price the board pays.<br>
  That being said i read this tidbit...<br>
<br>
<br>
First goto MY Control Center in EzBoard<br>
goto<br>
MY Preferences<br>
<br>
<br>
find this<br>
<br>
Max Number Of Replies Per Page <br>
(a box with numbers)<br>
This determines how many posts you will see in each screen when viewing a topic. <br>
<br>
change the number - usually it is 25 - to say 100.<br>
<br>
now where BEFORE if a post had 100 replies you had to do 4 HITS on the site to read the whole thread, NOW, you have only 1 hit - a reduction of 75% on the number of hits YOU made on the site,<br>
<br>
for any thread that has more than 25 replies you have now reduced your Personal hit count by atleast 50%.....<br>
<br>
now if everyone did that one SIMPLE thing...<br>
<br>
<br>
And i have now changed mine to 100 also. To some this may have been a known thing but to me i was unaware, so am posting this info incase others were clueless like i was. Hopefully any others who were also unaware can make this easy change to lower our Hit count.<br>
<br>
To those who were aware of this please disregard this message and maybe point others to this simple way we can conserve our boards costs.<br>
<br>
Also i just paid to be a EZsupporter which will further reduce the hits. Should kickin in a few days they say.<br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Dracthia SoulBlazer<br>
